    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Mechanism | Change Dyad Closure</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Change Dyad Closure</para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">What is a Dyad?</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">A <text styleclass="VariableName">Dyad</text> is two(2) <text styleclass="Element">Parts</text> and three(3) <text styleclass="Element">Joints</text>. <text styleclass="Body Text">Dyads</text> are also called <text styleclass="VariableName-IT">Assur Groups</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">A <text styleclass="VariableName">Dyad Closure</text> is one of two or more ways to assemble the two(2) <text styleclass="Element">parts</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> and </text><text styleclass="Element">Joints.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Use <text styleclass="T_Menu">Change Dyad Closure</text> - to re-assemble the <text styleclass="VariableName">Dyad</text> to the closure you want.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;"/></para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See more: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Dyad">Dyads</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Change Dyad Closure</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="4" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:30px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="text-align:right;"><image src="MD-Icon-ChangeDyadClosure.png" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"><title>Change Dyad Closure icon</title></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:middle;">
