        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-GA-RRR-Closure-01.png" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"><title>RRR Dyad - Closure 1</title><caption><![CDATA[RRR Dyad
Closure 1]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <list id="0" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="STEP %0:s: " format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="false" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo STEP" style="font-family:'Segoe UI Semibold'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo STEP"><text styleclass="Body Text">Do </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Change Dyad Closure </text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="PopupTable2" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:'Segoe UI Semibold'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="Bullets"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">Click</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;"> </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Kinematic-elements toolbar &gt; Change Dyad Closure</text><text styleclass="VariableName">. </text></li>
                  <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text style="font-weight:normal;">Click a</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Part-Outline" styleclass="Interface">Part-Outline</link><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> of one of the two(2) </text><text styleclass="Element">Parts </text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">in the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">dyad</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> with the</text> closure you want to change.<text styleclass="VariableName"> </text></li>
                  <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text style="font-style:normal;">Click</text> <image src="OK-tiny-11-15.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image> in the <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Command-Manager" styleclass="Interface">Command-Manager</link></li>
                </list>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">The <text styleclass="VariableName">Dyad</text> should now be in a different closure.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">If the <text styleclass="VariableName">Dyad</text> cannot assemble in the different closure, it will not move.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">If the <text styleclass="VariableName">Dyad</text> does not move:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="PopupTable2" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <list id="2" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="4" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:'Noto Sans'; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Do <text styleclass="Interface">1 to 3</text> again and again to find the closure you want.</li>
                </list>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName">Dyads have at least 2 and up to 4 Closures. </text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-GA-RRR-Closure-02.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><title>RRR Dyad - Closure 2</title><caption><![CDATA[RRR Dyad
Closure 2]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;"/></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Top-Tip:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">If there are many Dyads in the model, you can explore the Kinematics-Tree to help you identify each Dyad.</para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">In the Kinematics-Tree</para>
          <list id="3" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:'Segoe UI Semibold'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-style:normal;">Click and explore the </text><text styleclass="Interface" style="font-style:normal;">Kinematics-Tree</text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="font-style:normal;"> </text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text style="font-style:normal;">Click each</text> <text styleclass="VariableName">Dyad</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> </text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The </text><text styleclass="Element">Parts</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> and </text><text styleclass="Element">Joints</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> of each </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Dyad</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> become </text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">red</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> in the </text><text styleclass="Interface">graphic-area</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;"/></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_2"><anchor id="DyadClosure"><keywords><keyword>How to Change the Closure of a Dyad.</keyword><keyword>Change Dyad Closure</keyword></keywords></anchor><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image>Change the Closure of the RRP Dyad</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="5" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1" style="cell-padding:2px; border-width:0px; border-spacing:0px; border-collapse:collapse; cell-border-width:1px; border-color:#993300; border-style:solid; background-color:#f4f4f4;">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="VariableName-IT"><text styleclass="Body Text">The joints in the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">R-R-P</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> Dyad are: </text><text styleclass="VariableName">R</text><text styleclass="Body Text">evolute - </text><text styleclass="VariableName">R</text><text styleclass="Body Text">evolute - </text><text styleclass="VariableName">P</text><text styleclass="Body Text">rismatic</text></para>
                <para styleclass="VariableName-IT"><text styleclass="Body Text">In </text>MechDesigner<text styleclass="Body Text">, the joint names are: </text><text styleclass="VariableName">P</text><text styleclass="Body Text">in-Joint - </text><text styleclass="VariableName">P</text><text styleclass="Body Text">in-Joint - </text><text styleclass="VariableName">S</text><text styleclass="Body Text">lide-Joint.</text></para>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="VariableName-IT"><text styleclass="Body Text">The image below shows an </text>Offset-Slider-Crank<text styleclass="Body Text"> mechanism.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The <text styleclass="Interface">Motion-Part</text><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image> is a <text styleclass="Interface">Crank/Rocker.</text> </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">To help see the different closures, the <text styleclass="Interface">Crank/Rocker</text><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image> is fixed at a position that is at 90º to the inclined <text styleclass="Element">Line</text>. </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="page-break-inside:avoid;"><image src="MD-RRP-4Closures-schematic.ipp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Element">Part</text><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Body Text"> is connected to the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Crank/Rocker</text><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Body Text"> at </text><text styleclass="VariableName">R</text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="font-size:10pt; vertical-align:baseline;">1.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">The </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">end-Point </text><text styleclass="Body Text">of </text><text styleclass="Element">Part</text><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Body Text"> can be anywhere on the </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="color:#ff0000;">red circle</text><text styleclass="Body Text">. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Element">Part</text><image src="Red-14-3.gif" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image> is a <text styleclass="Element">Slide-Joint</text>. The <text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="color:#ff0000;">red circle</text> intersects the <text styleclass="Element">Slide-Joint</text> at two(2) places </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">However, the <text styleclass="Element">Pin-Joint</text><text styleclass="Body Text">,</text> <text styleclass="VariableName">R</text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="font-size:10pt; vertical-align:baseline;">2,</text> is offset from the <text styleclass="Element">Slide-Joint</text>. Thus, the <text styleclass="Element">Pin-Joint</text>, <text styleclass="VariableName">R</text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="font-size:10pt; vertical-align:baseline;">2,</text> must be on one of two(2) parallel lines: one line above and one line below the <text styleclass="Element">Slide-Joint.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The <text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="color:#ff0000;">red circle</text> intersects each line in two(2) places.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">Thus, the </text><text styleclass="Element">Pin-Joint,</text> <text styleclass="VariableName">R</text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="font-size:10pt; vertical-align:baseline;">2, </text><text styleclass="Body Text">can be at 4 places. This gives this </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Offset Slider-Crank</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> has 4 possible closures.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:220px;">
          <para styleclass="Interface"><image src="MD-Icon-ChangeDyadClosure.png" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"><title>Change Dyad Closure icon</title></image></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-GA-ClosureRRP2.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="HowTo STEP"><text styleclass="VariableName">Change the Dyad Closure</text></para>
          <list id="4" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="STEP %0:s: " format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo STEP" style="font-family:'Segoe UI Semibold'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo STEP">Click a <text styleclass="Interface">Part-Outline</text> in the <text styleclass="VariableName">R-R-P Dyad</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT"> </text><text styleclass="VariableName">(</text><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="VariableName" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="VariableName"> or </text><image src="Red-14-3.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="VariableName" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="VariableName">) </text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo NO STEP"><text style="font-style:normal;">Click </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Kinematic-elements-toolbar" styleclass="T_Menu">Kinematic-elements toolbar</link><text styleclass="T_Menu"> &gt; Change Dyad Closure</text><text styleclass="VariableName"> </text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo STEP"><text style="font-style:normal;">Click</text> <image src="OK-tiny-11-15.png" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image> <text styleclass="Body Text">in the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Command Manager</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text style="font-style:normal;">The Closure will usually change immediately. However, it is possible the Dyad cannot connect the joints when in a different closure.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text style="font-style:normal;">If the </text><text styleclass="Element">Parts</text><text style="font-style:normal;"> do not move, do </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Steps 1-3</text><text style="font-style:normal;"> again and again.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Notes">Notes<text styleclass="Body Text">:</text></para>
          <list id="5" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text style="font-style:normal;">It is possible that the Dyad is in a closure that cannot physically connect the Joints. In this case, when you cycle the mechanism, the Joints will &apos;brake&apos;. In this case, </text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-style:normal;">do </text><text styleclass="VariableName">STEP 1 - 3</text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-style:normal;"> again to find if the joints can assemble</text><text style="font-style:normal;">.</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
